RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOFTY COWTOWN surged to the front three wide nearing the turn, set the balance of the pace and widened through the stretch under strong handling to win as much the best. VAMONOS PIACENTE close along inside from the start, offered a mild bid in the four path entering the stretch and finished second best. HALO EFFECT unhurried early, had a mild late rally in the six path. MOST ADORABLE set the early pace along the inside, remained a sharp threat into the stretch and weakened late. THE KID'S PRAYER pressed the early pace two wide and was through after a half.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAR ENTERTAINER never far back, rallied determinedly along the rail under left handed urging through the stretch and got up in the final strides. QUARANTINO set the early pace along the inside, shifted outside after giving up the lead, had his heels clipped at the even sixteenths pole then tired in the stretch. RED COMET was no threat. DOWNTOWN CONNECTOR was no factor. ON SPOT stalked the early pace in the four path, was in tight between rivals while lacking room bumping with PERMAFROST to his outside then clipped heels with QUARANTINO to his inside at the seven sixteenths pole, fell and was walked off. THE STEWARDS POSTED THE INQUIRY SIGN AND AFTER REVIEW UPHELD THE ORIGINAL ORDER OF FINISH.
